snippet.title: The Real Reason Amber Heard Could End Up Behind Bars
snippet.description:
The Amber Heard and Johnny Depp divorce saga is, unfortunately, getting uglier and taking new twists and turns as each unveils new allegations against the other.

Heard filed for divorce from Depp in May 2016 and even obtained a temporary restraining order against Depp. Even though Depp and Heard reached a settlement in August of 2016, a recent report by International Business Times has revealed that Heard could face three years behind bars.

This report comes after Depp sued Heard for defamation over abuse claims. We’ve made a video that looks into the real reason Amber Heard could end up behind bars. Watch the video to find out!

#AmberHeard #JohnnyDepp #Relationship
